{
  "proposal": {
    "title": "Add Specs: ORIGYN",
    "description": "Adding new specification support for relaying ORIGYN data on Lava, served via the Internet Computer (ICP) public HTTP interface exposed by boundary nodes (icp-api.io). ORIGYN has no independent L1; it is a suite of canisters on the IC and its node-RPC surface is the IC Interface Specification HTTPS interface with CBOR-encoded bodies. Network identity is the IC root public key returned by GET /api/v2/status (there is no numeric chain-id); the chain-id verification is anchored on that endpoint on a best-effort basis, noting that response bodies are CBOR and the standard result parser cannot decode CBOR. State selection (block/height) is carried inside the CBOR request body rather than in the URL path, so there is no URL-level positional block argument and no block-number-indexed wire method to anchor block-tracking or archive/pruning directives.",
